<div id="review_1710493133" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1710493133" />
    <a title="Julia Buckley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2710358-julia-buckley"><img alt="Julia Buckley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1500142324p2/2710358.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1710493133?book_show_action=true">Jul 27, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julia Buckley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julia Buckley" href="/user/show/2710358-julia-buckley">Julia Buckley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1710493133" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18409696185541208843">This was the first play I&apos;ve read by Wilson, and I was struck by the depth of his characters and the power of his dialogue. His careful attention to the details and nuances of human speech and behavior made the conversations (and the characters) come alive on the page. Occasionally funny, often sad, this drama takes on a seemingly simple conflict that escalates into something much more for the brother and sister on either side of the argument.</span>
  <span id="freeText18409696185541208843" style="display:none">This was the first play I've read by Wilson, and I was struck by the depth of his characters and the power of his dialogue. His careful attention to the details and nuances of human speech and behavior made the conversations (and the characters) come alive on the page. Occasionally funny, often sad, this drama takes on a seemingly simple conflict that escalates into something much more for the brother and sister on either side of the argument.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18409696185541208843" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
