        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1841497322" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8618243885252038182">This is the fourth play in August Wilson&apos;s Century Cycle. This play was good. It was set in the 1930s and is about a man name Boy Willie who goes up north to Pittsburgh with his friend Lymon with intentions to sell the family piano in order to buy some land back south. Boy Willie&apos;s sister Berniece keeps the piano in her house and does not want to sell it. Tensions rise between the siblings until its dramatic conclusion. <br/><br/>As of this writing, out of the four Wilson plays that I have read I still th</span>
  <span id="freeText8618243885252038182" style="display:none">This is the fourth play in August Wilson's Century Cycle. This play was good. It was set in the 1930s and is about a man name Boy Willie who goes up north to Pittsburgh with his friend Lymon with intentions to sell the family piano in order to buy some land back south. Boy Willie's sister Berniece keeps the piano in her house and does not want to sell it. Tensions rise between the siblings until its dramatic conclusion. <br /><br />As of this writing, out of the four Wilson plays that I have read I still think "Ma Rainey's Black Bottom" is the best one. Next up: Seven Guitars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8618243885252038182" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

